/tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b734\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-733\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b733\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Hot Crowler &amp; Growler Fills<p>Benchtop Dolcita Brochachosaurus Hazy IPA</p><p>The Answer Ride 2 Richmond Hazy IPA</p><p>Brainstorm Rio de Oro Mexican Lager</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b599\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b579\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/b617c69b-7621-c8cf-f4ce-036241f6141f.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/b617c69b-7621-c8cf-f4ce-036241f6141f.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-723\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b723\"><table id=\"section_bd2d2b64b5dcfdfc09fae6dffd7fc2b4\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--44\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-28\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--56\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b722\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-721\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-580\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b580\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span>New wines in the door!</span><p><strong><span>Sophie Schaal Alsace Riesling: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Sophie Schaal brings us a classic Alsace Riesling - check out Julie’s wine write-up below for all the details!</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Domaine de Chantemerle Chablis: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Grandpa Boudin was a cooper, but his son hated the cooperage business so when he started making Chablis he refused to use barrels. His son, Francis, carries on the tradition of \"barrel free Chablis\" to allow for the purest expression of Chardonnay. Lively lemon and citrus pair with white flowers and a chalky minerality, finished with just the right amount of texture. Practicing sustainable, hand harvested, native yeast, unfiltered, unfined.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Chateau de Crezancy Sancerre: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Coming from a family-run estate, Crezancy Sancerre is one of only a few château-bottled Sancerres in existence. Elegant and classic with crisp citrus, lingering minerality and a touch of white pepper on the finish.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Coste di Brenta Trebbiano d'Abruzzo: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>A family vineyard, all of the wine from Coste di Brenta is hand-crafted and organically made. This Trebbiano is beautifully textured, lively and oh so easy to drink with notes of grapefruit and apple. You'll find me buying one, two, or three... bottles for myself.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Chateau La Genestière \"Les Galets\" Rose: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Fresh and vibrant, Les Galets comes from a southern France estate located just outside the Rose powerhouse region of Tavel. A beautiful salmon pink in color, Les Galets hits first with bright red fruit and floral notes, followed quickly by a firmly balanced minerality. Nuance abounds in this excellent value French crusher. Sustainable.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Colombaio Chianti Classico: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Our favorite Italian-focused distributor, Alek, pointed us to this loveable Classico. Colombaio di Cencio was born in 1993 when German entrepreneur Werner Ernst Wilhelm was so captivated by the beauty of Chianti that he transformed a historic country house into a winery. Bursting with cherry, red currant and violet with a soft, fresh finish.</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b724\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b416\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/fd6dba5e-c19a-be63-8408-2e2a21c7a2c4.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/fd6dba5e-c19a-be63-8408-2e2a21c7a2c4.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-415\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b415\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Wine we’re drinking this week:<p><span><span><span>I bet you're shocked to see a wine writeup on an Alsatian White and it's not coming from Beth. Yes, I stole her thunder on this one because, well, it's just that good. </span></span></span></p><p><span><span><span>Sophie Schaal was born in Burgundy, but she credits South Africa with really lighting the fire of her wine journey, as it was the place that broadened her horizons and helped her to take her oenology degree to the next level. Today she splits time between France and South Africa and makes some banging wines from both regions.</span></span></span></p><p><strong><span><span><span>Sophie Schaal Riesling</span></span></span></strong><span><span><span> is classic Alsace. If you need an intro to Alsatian whites, start here. Notes of green apple, citrus, slate, and minerality are all hallmarks of Alsatian Riesling but the zesty acidity is what makes the region famous. Sophie Schaal lets all those classic notes shine in this intensely aromatic and wonderfully dry Riesling. We've had plenty of dry Riesling here in the shop, but Sophie Schaal grabbed my attention in a way many others don't. Nuanced and complex while also being so damn easy to drink - this bottle is for everyone.</span></span></span></p><p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Julie.</span></span></span></span></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b508\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-452\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b452\"><table id=\"section_86128f5a126f7e81a02da43f945a46f7\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--35\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-10\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--47\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b456\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-455\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b453\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/7aaabe8a-323a-a350-eaab-acf9366b6803.jpeg\" width=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/7aaabe8a-323a-a350-eaab-acf9366b6803.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"533.8\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:533.8px;width:533.8px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-454\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b454\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span>May Tasting Events are spring ready!</span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b457\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-177\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b177\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Thanks for your business! See you soon, Beth, Julie &amp; Aidan and the entire Brew Crew</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]><table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"660\" style=\"width:660px;\"><tr><td><![endif]--><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--33\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b9\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--6\"><table><tbody><tr></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b15\"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody></table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>",
